rfcs/0296-structured-logging.md
   502â†’### Don't break anything
   503â†’
   504â†’Allow structured logging to be added in the current `0.4.x` series of `log`. This gives us the option of including structured logging in an `0.4.x` release, or bumping the minor crate version without introducing any actual breaking changes.
   505â†’
  1598â†’#### Build a serialization contract in `log`
  1599â†’
  1600â†’Instead of internalizing a few serialization frameworks, `log` could provide a public common contract for them to conform to:
  1601â†’
  1602â†’```rust
  1603â†’// Instead of `Value::from_any` + `FromAny`
  1604â†’
  1605â†’pub trait Visit {
  1606â†’    fn visit(&self, visitor: &mut dyn Visitor) -> Result<(), Error>;
  1607â†’}
  1608â†’
  1609â†’pub trait Visitor {
  1610â†’    fn u64(&mut self, v: u64) -> Result<(), Error>;
  1611â†’    fn i64(&mut self, v: i64) -> Result<(), Error>;
  1612â†’
  1613â†’    ..
  1614â†’}
  1615â†’```
